The Sudanese government has been under pressure from the international community to change its laws. In 2016, the United Nations Human Rights Council passed a resolution calling on Sudan to decriminalize abortion in cases of rape, incest, and when the mother’s life is in danger. The resolution also called on Sudan to ensure that women and girls have access to safe and legal abortion services.

The Sudanese government has not yet responded to the resolution.
